a.id_product as id, COUNT(pa.id_product_attribute) as variations
This interface allows you to manage product stock and their variations.
Through this interface, you can increase and decrease product stock for an given warehouse.
Furthermore, you can alter product quantities between warehouses, or within one warehouse.
If you want to increase quantities of multiple products at once, you can use the "Supply orders" page under the "Stock" menu.
Finally, you need to provide the quantity that you'll be adding:
Usable for sale means that this quantity will be available in your shop(s),
otherwise it will be considered reserved (i.e. for other purposes).
You must choose a warehouses before adding stock. See Stock/Warehouses
